'''Radik Isayev''' (born September 26, 1989 in Ukhul, [[Akhtynsky District]], [[Dagestan]]) is a [[Russia]]n-born naturalized [[Azerbaijan]]i [[taekwondo]] practitioner of [[Lezgins|Lezgi]] origin. He won the gold medal at the [[2014 European Taekwondo Championships|2014 European Championships]] Men's 87&nbsp;kg,<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:Азербайджанский таэквондист Радик Исаев стал чемпионом Европы |url=http://www.1news.az/sport/others/20140502053600715.html|publisher=1news.az|accessdate=2 May 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> also he won bronze in [[2013 World Taekwondo Championships|2013 World Championships]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Azerbaijani taekwondo fighter grabs bronze medal in Mexican World Champions |url=http://news.az/articles/sports/81288|publisher=news.az|accessdate=22 July 2013}}</ref> Radik also won a gold medal at the 2016 Summer Olympics held in Rio.

